                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 49</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Choi<br/>(Coauthors: Senators Alvarado-Gil, Archuleta, Arreguín, Cabaldon, Dahle, Durazo, Gonzalez, Grayson, Hurtado, Jones, Laird, McNerney, Niello, Ochoa Bogh, Padilla, Richardson, Seyarto, Strickland, Umberg, Valladares, Wahab, Weber Pierson, and Wiener)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>May 28, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to the 75th anniversary of the Korean War.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SR 49, Choi.
                          </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"/></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_94A305EF-9FE4-4C75-A350-B094E52DD0DF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Korean War began on June 25, 1950, when North Korean forces crossed the 38th parallel and invaded the Republic of Korea, marking the start of a three-year conflict; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B7DB94CD-9F7C-40AC-B861-5D7D2B42BFBB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On June 27, 1950, President Harry S. Truman ordered the Armed Forces of the United States to help the Republic of Korea defend itself against the North Korean invasion; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D97C4933-9FA7-4C81-B197-D1CD1B4892FA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Korean War ended with the signing of the Korean Armistice Agreement on July 27, 1953, which halted hostilities without a formal peace treaty and left the Korean Peninsula divided to this day; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_826BF27B-9AFB-45E3-8382-810CC593D417"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, More than 1,800,000 American men and women served in the Korean War, with over 36,000 losing their lives and more than 100,000 wounded in the defense of freedom and democracy; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A6D48E29-483C-4306-83E3-1074571A7276"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The bravery, sacrifice, and commitment of Korean War veterans have too often been overlooked, and they should be rightfully remembered as part of the “Forgotten War”; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BFA50C9C-F8D0-4038-AA82-CB75CA018E14"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In the 75 years since the outbreak of the Korean War, the Republic of Korea has emerged from a war-torn economy into one of the major economies in the world and one of the United States’ largest trading partners; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8C256A29-69A6-4129-A9AB-D57073398F63"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Republic of Korea is among the closest allies of the United States, having contributed troops in support of United States during the Vietnam War, the Gulf War, and its operations in Iraq and Afghanistan, while also supporting numerous United Nations peacekeeping missions throughout the world; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0074865B-1690-4D17-AA68-03F81FB17210"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The strong alliance between the Republic of Korea and the United States remains a lasting legacy of the sacrifices made during the Korean War; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_38725187-58AA-445A-9535-1DB14C8291F2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, That the State of California commemorates June 25, 2025, as the 75th anniversary of the Korean War to honor the courage, service, and sacrifice of all who served during the Korean War; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_7F87FA1B-4B24-4847-B190-3C477DD80359"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
